qas.question: In what historical period did Southampton expand greatly?
What year was the Southampton Docks company created?
In what month of 1838 was stone laid for the foundation of the Southampton docks?
What year did the railroad to London from Southampton open fully?
What name did Southampton earn for its importance in creating a link to London?

context: The town experienced major expansion during the <a0_0>Victorian era<a0_0/>. The Southampton Docks company had been formed in <a1_0>1835<a1_0/>. In <a2_0>October<a2_0/> 1838 the foundation stone of the docks was laid and the first dock opened in 1842. The structural and economic development of docks continued for the next few decades. The railway link to London was fully opened in May <a3_0>1840<a3_0/>. Southampton subsequently became known as <a4_0>The Gateway to the Empire<a4_0/>.
